01:40.839 --> 01:46.845
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS,
I'M ALWAYS HERE ♪

02:10.259 --> 02:12.044
-YOU WANTED TO
SEE ME, MISTER MAHORN?

02:13.916 --> 02:16.048
-OUR LAST SHIPMENT
WAS SHORT, ZEKE.

02:17.789 --> 02:19.748
A DOZEN RIFLES SHORT.

02:21.010 --> 02:22.838
-COME ON, YOU DON'T THINK
I'D STEAL FROM YOU, DO YOU?

02:24.013 --> 02:26.233
[LAUGHS] COME ON.
I'M NOT THAT STUPID!

02:26.363 --> 02:28.887
-I DON'T THINK, ZEKE. I KNOW.

02:30.324 --> 02:32.804
-NO! COME ON,
MR MAHORN, PLEASE.
YOU'VE GOTTA LET ME FIND THEM.

02:32.935 --> 02:33.936
PLEASE, PLEASE!

02:39.246 --> 02:40.986
-OKAY, LET'S GET OUTTA HERE.

02:49.256 --> 02:51.606
-SUMMER: BAYWATCH TO SCARAB ONE.

02:51.736 --> 02:53.477
STEPHANIE, IT'S SUMMER.

02:53.608 --> 02:55.479
WE JUST GOT A CALL OVER THE
EMERGENCY DISTRESS CHANNEL.

02:56.088 --> 02:57.699
A PILOT ON APPROACH TO
SANTA MONICA AIRPORT

02:57.829 --> 03:00.310
THINKS HE SPOTTED A BODY
FLOATING IN THE WATER,

03:00.441 --> 03:02.312
TEN MILES WEST OF VISTA POINT.

03:02.443 --> 03:04.053
-WE GOT IT, WE'RE ON OUR WAY.

03:12.888 --> 03:13.976
OVER THERE!

03:29.339 --> 03:30.688
-IT'S THE COASTGUARD.

03:30.819 --> 03:32.821
THEY MUST HAVE PICKED
UP THE DISTRESS CALL.

03:54.234 --> 03:55.626
STEPHANIE, WHAT'S WRONG?

03:59.151 --> 04:01.719
-BAYWATCH SCARAB, THIS
IS COASTGUARD COPTER
SIX-FIVE-FOUR-THREE.

04:01.850 --> 04:03.112
COME IN, BAYWATCH.

04:03.243 --> 04:04.156
-GO AHEAD, THIS IS SCARAB.

04:04.940 --> 04:07.072
-STAND DOWN, REPEAT,
DO NOT PROCEED.

04:07.203 --> 04:08.030
STAND DOWN AT ONCE.

04:08.160 --> 04:09.074
-TEN-FOUR.

04:09.901 --> 04:13.905
STEPHANIE, I GOTTA
CUT THE ENGINES.

04:20.260 --> 04:21.478
-RESCUE CHECK COMPLETE, SIR.

04:24.829 --> 04:26.396
SWIMMER'S READY.

04:26.527 --> 04:27.658
-DEPLOY SWIMMER.

04:27.789 --> 04:29.443
-ROGER.

04:39.366 --> 04:40.280
SWIMMER'S OKAY.

04:40.410 --> 04:42.891
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

06:10.457 --> 06:13.721
-PETTY OFFICE SCOTT DANIELS,
UNITED STATES COASTGUARD.

06:13.851 --> 06:16.245
-LIEUTENANT STEPHANIE
HOLDEN, LA COUNTY LIFEGUARD.

06:16.376 --> 06:18.203
THIS IS MY COLLEAGUE,
MATT BRODY.

06:19.553 --> 06:20.989
-WE RADIOED AHEAD
FOR AN AMBULANCE.

06:21.119 --> 06:23.078
THE VICTIM'S BEEN TRANSPORTED
TO THE EMERGENCY ROOM.

06:23.208 --> 06:24.514
LOOKS LIKE HE'S GONNA MAKE IT.

06:25.123 --> 06:26.386
-WHY DID YOU ORDER
US TO STAND DOWN?

06:26.995 --> 06:28.431
-YOU WERE HEADING FOR A
LARGE CHUNK OF THAT FISH NET

06:29.084 --> 06:30.390
THE VICTIM WAS WRAPPED IN.

06:30.520 --> 06:31.913
YOU COULDN'T SEE
IT FROM YOUR BOAT.

06:32.043 --> 06:33.349
WE COULD SEE
IT FROM THE AIR.

06:33.480 --> 06:34.785
IT WOULD HAVE
FOULED YOUR SCREWS,

06:34.916 --> 06:36.874
DISABLED YOU, AND
PULLED THE VICTIM UNDER.

06:37.005 --> 06:38.485
-HEY SCOTT, LET'S GO!

06:39.137 --> 06:40.574
-SEE YOU AROUND, LIEUTENANT.

07:03.640 --> 07:04.989
-HEY.
-HEY.

07:05.120 --> 07:08.036
-HI, CHIEF THORPE
REVIEWED MY REPORT

07:08.166 --> 07:09.603
ON OUR JOINT OPERATION
WITH THE COASTGUARD.

07:10.212 --> 07:12.214
HE AGREES THAT OUR
PROCEDURES NEED IMPROVING,

07:12.344 --> 07:14.085
SO THEN WE'RE GOING
TO BE PARTICIPATING IN

07:14.216 --> 07:16.218
AN EXCHANGE TRAINING
PROGRAM WITH THE COASTGUARD.

07:16.348 --> 07:17.175
-STARTING WHEN?

07:17.306 --> 07:18.699
-TODAY.

07:19.264 --> 07:20.875
A COASTIE WILL BE COMING HERE
TO LEARN MORE ABOUT OUR JOBS,

07:21.005 --> 07:22.050
AND THEN I'LL GO WORK WITH THEM.

07:22.746 --> 07:24.400
-SOUNDS LIKE FUN.

07:24.531 --> 07:26.184
HEY, MAYBE THEY'LL LET YOU
JUMP OUT OF A HELICOPTER.

07:29.492 --> 07:31.276
-HEY, LOOK AT THAT GUY SWIM!

07:51.993 --> 07:53.255
-OH NO.

07:53.385 --> 07:54.604
-WHAT? WHO IS IT?

07:56.258 --> 07:57.694
-SUPERMAN.

07:59.609 --> 08:00.436
HAVE FUN.

08:00.567 --> 08:01.611
-[SIGH]

08:04.745 --> 08:06.790
-PETTY OFFICER DANIELS
REPORTING FOR DUTY.

08:07.835 --> 08:09.010
-WELCOME TO BAYWATCH.

08:09.140 --> 08:10.533
-THANKS.

08:10.664 --> 08:11.882
-YOU'VE MET MATT BRODY.
-SCOTT: YEAH, HI.

08:12.013 --> 08:13.493
-AND THIS IS SUMMER QUINN.

08:13.623 --> 08:14.581
-HI.

08:14.711 --> 08:15.669
SO WHERE'D YOU SWIM FROM?

08:16.278 --> 08:17.192
-REDONDO BEACH.

08:17.888 --> 08:19.629
IT'S ABOUT FOUR MILES.

08:19.760 --> 08:22.110
I USUALLY SWIM SIX, BUT I
WANTED TO SAVE MY STRENGTH.

08:23.981 --> 08:25.722
I'M SURE I'VE GOT A
GRUELING DAY AHEAD OF ME.

08:31.902 --> 08:34.339
-I CAN'T BELIEVE THEY
ACTUALLY GET PAID TO DO THIS!

08:36.298 --> 08:37.559
[SCOFFS]

08:42.783 --> 08:44.306
WHAT'S THAT OLD
LIFEGUARD SLOGAN,

08:45.133 --> 08:48.179
IT'S NOT JUST A JOB,
IT'S A VACATION.

08:48.789 --> 08:49.833
[LAUGHS]

08:50.486 --> 08:51.748
WOW.

08:51.879 --> 08:53.576
-WELL, UNLIKE YOU PEOPLE,
WE DON'T SIT AROUND

08:53.707 --> 08:55.491
DRINKING COFFEE, WAITING
FOR THE PHONE TO RING.

08:55.622 --> 08:58.146
WE HAVE TO MAINTAIN A
CONSTANT STATE OF READINESS.

08:58.276 --> 08:59.843
AND THEN REACT INSTANTLY.

09:00.975 --> 09:02.846
WITHOUT THE BENEFIT OF
ALL YOUR FANCY TOYS,

09:02.977 --> 09:03.847
I MIGHT ADD.

09:04.544 --> 09:06.371
THIS IS AS HIGH-TECH
AS WE GET AROUND HERE.

09:07.851 --> 09:10.158
YOUR RESCUE CAN IS NOT
JUST A LIFE-SAVING DEVICE.

09:11.159 --> 09:13.204
YOU MAY NEED IT FOR
SELF-DEFENSE AS WELL.

09:14.728 --> 09:16.730
NOT ALL THE ACTION ON THE
BEACH HAPPENS IN THE WATER.

09:17.426 --> 09:18.906
YOU JUST AS EASILY MIGHT
FIND YOURSELF IN THE

09:19.036 --> 09:21.430
MIDDLE OF ANYTHING
FROM A LOVERS' QUARREL,

09:22.126 --> 09:23.258
TO A GANG WAR.

09:30.570 --> 09:32.789
EXCUSE ME, PETTY OFFICE DANIELS.

09:32.920 --> 09:34.312
I TAKE MY JOB VERY SERIOUSLY,

09:34.443 --> 09:36.053
AND I EXPECT YOU TO DO THE SAME.

09:37.707 --> 09:39.143
-WELL, EXCUSE ME, LIEUTENANT.

09:39.274 --> 09:40.580
BUT YOU'RE NOT DEALING WITH SOME

09:40.710 --> 09:42.364
FRESH OFF THE SWIM
TEAM ROOKIE HERE.

09:43.365 --> 09:45.846
LIKE YOURSELF, I'M A HIGHLY
TRAINED PROFESSIONAL.

09:45.976 --> 09:47.717
AND I HAVE SPENT MUCH
OF MY LAST FIVE YEARS

09:47.848 --> 09:50.111
AIRLIFTING OIL WORKERS
OFF BURNING DERRICKS

09:50.241 --> 09:51.286
IN THE GULF OF MEXICO.

09:52.461 --> 09:54.419
PULLING FISHERMEN
FROM THE BERING SEA.

09:55.464 --> 09:56.770
DIVERS OFF THE CARIBBEAN REEFS.

09:58.032 --> 10:00.469
HIKERS HANGING OFF
CLIFFS AT BIG SUR.

10:01.296 --> 10:03.907
SO I THINK I KNOW A THING OR
TWO ABOUT MAKING A RESCUE.

10:04.038 --> 10:04.821
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

10:04.952 --> 10:06.475
WHAT'S GOING ON?

10:11.132 --> 10:12.002
-HEY!

10:13.090 --> 10:14.135
-HEY, WATCH IT, MAN!

10:14.265 --> 10:17.747
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

10:29.977 --> 10:31.500
-STAY WHERE YOU ARE!
-I CAN'T TOUCH THE BOTTOM!

10:31.631 --> 10:33.110
-YOU'RE IN A RIP CURRENT.

10:35.025 --> 10:36.374
-LET'S GET OUT OF HERE!

10:36.505 --> 10:38.202
-I GOT YOU; YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.

10:45.296 --> 10:46.515
NICE OF YOU TO JOIN US.

10:49.213 --> 10:50.084
-LET ME TAKE HIM IN.

10:51.128 --> 10:52.521
COME ON.

10:53.740 --> 10:55.829
YOU'RE OKAY, COME ON.

11:12.106 --> 11:13.673
-WAIT, I DIDN'T
ORDER THIS, SUMMER.

11:13.803 --> 11:15.283
-I KNOW.

11:15.413 --> 11:17.633
IT'S COMPLIMENTS OF PETTY
OFFICER SCOTT DANIELS.

11:17.764 --> 11:19.896
UNITED STATES COASTGUARD.

11:27.077 --> 11:29.645
YOU GOTTA ADMIT,
STEPHANIE, HE'S GOT STYLE.

11:31.516 --> 11:33.040
-MIND IF I JOIN YOU?

11:35.259 --> 11:37.305
LOOK, I WANT TO
APOLOGIZE FOR COMING ON

11:37.435 --> 11:38.872
LIKE SUCH A JERK TODAY.

11:39.829 --> 11:41.657
EVERY NOW AND THEN MY
RESCUE SWIMMER'S EGO

11:41.788 --> 11:42.876
RAISES ITS UGLY HEAD.

11:44.312 --> 11:45.661
-DOES THIS MEAN THAT
YOU'RE ADMITTING THAT

11:45.792 --> 11:46.749
THERE'S MORE TO BEING
A LIFEGUARD THAN

11:46.880 --> 11:48.359
JUST GETTING THE PERFECT TAN?

11:48.882 --> 11:50.361
-I'LL ADMIT IT'S
NOT AS EASY AS IT LOOKS.

11:51.188 --> 11:53.495
I'LL BE HONEST, I DIDN'T
HAVE A CLUE WHO WAS

11:53.625 --> 11:54.931
THE VICTIM OUT THERE TODAY.

11:55.062 --> 11:57.281
-WELL, MAYBE NOW YOU'LL
RESPECT WHAT WE DO.

11:57.891 --> 11:58.935
-WITHOUT QUESTION.

11:59.544 --> 12:01.721
-AND YOU'LL STOP
REFERRING TO LIFEGUARDS AS

12:01.851 --> 12:03.940
LAND WEENIES AND SAND PEEPS.

12:04.071 --> 12:09.554
-[LAUGHS] NEVER AGAIN WILL
THOSE WORDS EVER PASS MY LIPS.

12:11.121 --> 12:12.644
-GOOD.

12:17.998 --> 12:21.479
-LOOK, I REALIZE WE GOT
OFF ON THE WRONG FOOT,

12:23.743 --> 12:25.527
BUT I REALLY WOULD LIKE IF
WE COULD BECOME FRIENDS.

12:31.315 --> 12:33.491
-WELL, I'M WILLING TO
LEAVE OPEN THAT POSSIBILITY.

12:34.275 --> 12:35.189
-GOOD.

12:38.322 --> 12:41.151
-I'M SURE BENEATH
ALL THAT MACHO BLUSTER

12:41.282 --> 12:42.892
THERE'S A WARM,
SENSITIVE SIDE OF YOU

12:43.023 --> 12:44.807
JUST CRYING OUT FOR EQUAL TIME.

12:45.808 --> 12:47.114
-YOU READ ME LIKE A BOOK.

12:50.726 --> 12:52.206
AND I'LL BET YOU
LIKE CHINESE FOOD.

12:54.904 --> 12:56.776
-[LAUGHS] I LOVE CHINESE FOOD.

12:58.865 --> 13:01.171
BUT I START MY COASTGUARD
TRAINING TOMORROW,

13:01.302 --> 13:03.870
SO I HAVE TO GET A
GOOD NIGHT'S SLEEP.

13:06.524 --> 13:07.874
THANKS FOR THE ROOT BEER.

13:09.527 --> 13:11.181
SEE YOU IN THE MORNING.

13:11.312 --> 13:12.226
-FIRST THING.

13:12.356 --> 13:13.488
-BYE-BYE.

13:15.533 --> 13:16.621
-BYE.

13:16.752 --> 13:18.275
-SO, HOW'D IT GO?

13:18.406 --> 13:21.365
-[SIGH] WELL, IF SHE LOOKS
BACK, SHE'S INTERESTED.

13:34.683 --> 13:36.598
I GUESS THAT ONLY WORKS
IF YOU'RE CLINT EASTWOOD.

13:37.338 --> 13:38.469
SO, WHAT ARE YOU DOING TONIGHT?

13:38.600 --> 13:39.557
-[LAUGHS]

14:01.101 --> 14:02.015
-I'LL GET HER.

14:05.757 --> 14:06.715
-THANKS FOR THE RIDE.

14:06.846 --> 14:07.847
-GIVE THEM HELL, STEPH.

14:09.022 --> 14:10.371
-I'LL GET THAT.

14:10.501 --> 14:11.763
-OKAY.

14:11.894 --> 14:13.200
DID YOU GET A GOOD
NIGHT'S SLEEP?

14:13.330 --> 14:14.549
-YES, I DID.

14:14.679 --> 14:15.898
-YOU MISSED A GOOD DINNER.

14:17.204 --> 14:17.987
CHIEF'S RIGHT UP HERE.

14:18.118 --> 14:19.032
-OKAY.

14:26.648 --> 14:29.477
-CHIEF, THIS IS LIEUTENANT
STEPHANIE HOLDEN.

14:29.607 --> 14:31.348
SHE'S THE LIFEGUARD I
WAS TELLING YOU ABOUT.

14:31.479 --> 14:33.611
-HEARD YOU HAD TO PULL HIS
FAT OUT OF THE FIRE YESTERDAY.

14:35.396 --> 14:37.485
ABOUT TIME SOMEBODY
PUT HIM IN HIS PLACE.

14:39.008 --> 14:39.966
-NICE TO MEET YOU, CHIEF.

14:40.096 --> 14:40.880
-WELCOME TO THE COASTGUARD.

14:41.010 --> 14:42.838
-THANK YOU.

14:42.969 --> 14:44.231
-THE CHIEF WAS JUST
TELLING ME THAT THE VICTIM

14:44.361 --> 14:45.449
IN THE FISHNET ISN'T TALKING
ABOUT HOW HE GOT THERE.

14:46.189 --> 14:47.103
-WHY NOT?

14:47.234 --> 14:48.975
-HIS NAME IS ZEKE LAROUGE

14:49.105 --> 14:50.933
HE SHOWED UP AS A SUSPECTED
SMUGGLER IN THE EPIC FILES,

14:51.064 --> 14:52.543
BUT HE HASN'T BEEN CONVICTED.

14:52.674 --> 14:54.284
-SINCE WE ALREADY HAVE
YOUR SECURITY CLEARANCES,

14:54.415 --> 14:56.286
WE MAY AS WELL USE
THIS CASE AS PART OF

14:56.417 --> 14:58.288
YOUR FIRST COASTGUARD
TRAINING SESSION.

14:58.419 --> 15:00.116
LAW ENFORCEMENT.

15:00.247 --> 15:02.336
-ZEKE'S BEEN WORKING ON A
SUSPECTED SMUGGLING VESSEL.

15:02.466 --> 15:03.903
FISHING BOAT CALLED
THE LA PALOMA.

15:04.686 --> 15:06.122
-IT'S ON OUR LOOKOUT LIST.

15:06.253 --> 15:09.865
IT MEANS THAT SOME
AGENCY, THE ATF, FBI, DEA,

15:09.996 --> 15:11.823
CUSTOMS AND COASTGUARD HAS
A SPECIAL INTEREST IN THEM.

15:11.954 --> 15:13.260
REASON TO BELIEVE THEY'RE
DOING SOMETHING ELSE

15:13.390 --> 15:15.131
OTHER THAN FISHING.

15:15.262 --> 15:16.437
-SPOTTED THEM GOING SOUTH
OFF THE MEXICAN COAST,

15:16.567 --> 15:17.699
BUT IT WAS TOO ROUGH
FOR A BOARDING.

15:18.395 --> 15:19.353
-SO WHAT DO WE DO NOW?

15:20.180 --> 15:21.572
-WE KEEP WATCHING.

15:21.703 --> 15:23.792
LA PALOMA'S JUST ONE OF
MANY BOATS ON OUR LIST.

15:25.489 --> 15:27.883
OKAY, WELL NOW THAT
YOU GOT YOUR FEET WET,

15:28.014 --> 15:29.624
WE'LL MOVE ON TO SOME OF
THE OTHER THINGS THAT WE

15:29.754 --> 15:31.931
DO AROUND HERE WHEN
WE'RE NOT SITTING AROUND,

15:32.061 --> 15:34.672
DRINKING COFFEE, WAITING
FOR THE PHONE TO RING.

15:36.065 --> 15:40.809
-[ROCK SONG PLAYS]

15:54.605 --> 15:56.564
♪ HOLD UP DON'T TAKE FOR GRANTED

15:56.694 --> 15:58.435
♪ DON'T YOU MESS AROUND

15:58.566 --> 16:01.134
♪ I'LL MAKE YOU BEG FOR MERCY

16:01.264 --> 16:03.049
♪ THEN I'LL TAKE YOU DOWN

16:03.179 --> 16:05.181
♪ NO LIP YOUR TONGUE IS TWISTED

16:05.312 --> 16:07.531
♪ WHAT YOUR GOT TO SAY

16:07.662 --> 16:09.664
♪ SURRENDER ALL RESISTANCE

16:09.794 --> 16:11.318
♪ I'LL LET YOU WALK AWAY

16:11.448 --> 16:14.930
♪ YOU BET I WON'T BUT OH YES I CAN

16:15.757 --> 16:19.891
♪ YOU'LL NEVER FIND YOURSELF A BETTER MAN
♪

16:20.022 --> 16:24.984
♪ RISE BORN TO FIGHT

16:27.421 --> 16:30.424
♪ STAY ALIVE

16:31.686 --> 16:33.818
♪ REACH THE SKY

16:37.213 --> 16:39.520
♪ STAND UP, YOU WILL BE COUNTED,

16:39.650 --> 16:41.478
♪ WHATCHA YOU WANNA BE

16:41.609 --> 16:43.785
♪ TIME'S UP WHEN YOU'RE SURROUNDED

16:43.915 --> 16:45.047
♪ YOU BETTER FOLLOW ME

16:45.961 --> 16:48.094
♪ ZOOM OUT AND FOCUS IN ON

16:48.224 --> 16:50.052
♪ THERE'S SO MUCH TO LEARN

16:50.183 --> 16:52.489
♪ GOTTA SEND ME BACK TO SCHOOLIN

16:52.620 --> 16:54.709
♪ GONNA TAKE MY TURN

16:54.839 --> 16:58.365
♪ YOU BET I WON'T BUT OH YES I CAN

16:58.495 --> 17:02.760
♪ YOU'LL NEVER FIND YOURSELF A BETTER MAN
♪

17:02.891 --> 17:08.288
♪ RISE BORN TO FIGHT

17:10.203 --> 17:13.031
♪ STAY ALIVE

17:14.555 --> 17:16.035
♪ REACH THE SKY

17:17.210 --> 17:18.689
-BEFORE WE GO UP IN THE HELO,

17:18.819 --> 17:20.343
THERE'S JUST ONE MORE
AREA WE HAVE TO COVER.

17:21.648 --> 17:24.260
ONE OF THE MOST IMPORTANT
FUNCTIONS OF THE COASTGUARD

17:25.608 --> 17:28.089
IS THE MAINTENANCE OF
MARITIME NAVIGATIONAL AIDS.

17:36.055 --> 17:37.230
-GIVE ME A BREAK.

17:38.100 --> 17:39.841
-SEE THAT OPENING
AT THE BOTTOM?

17:39.971 --> 17:42.539
ALL YOU'VE GOT TO DO IS CLIMB
IN THERE WITH THE SHOVEL,

17:42.670 --> 17:43.714
START SCRAPING.

17:45.499 --> 17:46.717
-WHAT'S INSIDE?

17:46.848 --> 17:50.591
-OH, BARNACLES, SEAWEED, SLUDGE.

17:51.983 --> 17:53.376
YOU KNOW, YOU NAME IT.

17:53.507 --> 17:55.683
IF IT'S IN THE OCEAN,
IT'S IN THAT BUOY.

17:55.813 --> 17:56.945
-HERE YOU GO.

17:59.600 --> 18:00.905
-YOU'RE NOT REALLY
GONNA MAKE ME DO THIS?

18:01.036 --> 18:02.864
-OH YEAH.

18:02.994 --> 18:05.084
TUBING A BUOY IS A VITAL PART
OF THE COASTGUARD EXPERIENCE.

18:09.914 --> 18:12.091
-[LAUGHTER]

18:19.272 --> 18:20.490
-WHAT ARE YOU LOOKING AT?

18:20.621 --> 18:23.232
-[LAUGHTER]
-GOOD LUCK.

18:34.548 --> 18:35.592
-UGH.

18:42.425 --> 18:43.861
-[LAUGHTER]

18:43.992 --> 18:45.385
-[COUGHING]

18:53.958 --> 18:56.352
OW, OW, OW!

18:56.483 --> 18:57.788
OW!

19:00.139 --> 19:03.577
OW, SOMETHING IS BITING ME!

19:03.707 --> 19:06.145
-[LAUGHTER]

19:10.671 --> 19:12.934
A LITTLE COASTGUARD HUMOR?

19:13.935 --> 19:16.981
I WILL NEVER FORGIVE
YOU FOR THIS.

19:23.727 --> 19:25.642
[SIGHING]

19:36.044 --> 19:37.176
-STEPH.

19:40.396 --> 19:42.224
I TAKE IT YOU'VE FLOWN
IN A HELICOPTER BEFORE?

19:42.790 --> 19:43.878
-SURE.

19:45.009 --> 19:45.923
-YOU EVER JUMP OUT OF ONE?

19:46.881 --> 19:51.799
-NO, BUT I'VE JUMPED OFF A
PIER, BRIDGES, BOATS, CLIFFS.

19:52.495 --> 19:53.931
HEIGHTS AREN'T A PROBLEM FOR ME.

19:54.802 --> 19:56.804
-WELL, GOOD. LET'S DO IT.

19:57.631 --> 20:02.113
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

20:06.466 --> 20:08.381
IT GETS A LITTLE
CLAUSTROPHOBIC IN HERE.

20:10.296 --> 20:11.688
HOW ARE YOU HOLDING UP?

20:12.776 --> 20:13.777
-I'M FINE.

20:14.387 --> 20:15.997
-YOU REMEMBER ALL
THE HAND SIGNALS?

20:16.911 --> 20:18.086
-YES.

20:18.608 --> 20:19.479
-YOU'RE AWESOME.

20:31.447 --> 20:34.624
REMEMBER, WHEN YOU JUMP, KEEP
YOUR EYES ON THE HORIZON.

20:35.321 --> 20:37.584
BUT DO NOT LOSE
TRACK OF THE VICTIM.

20:50.945 --> 20:52.599
JUST A TRICKY CROSSWIND.

20:53.643 --> 20:55.166
STAY FOCUSED.

20:58.779 --> 21:00.302
OKAY, YOU'RE READY!

21:03.000 --> 21:05.046
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

21:28.417 --> 21:29.592
-LIEUTENANT!

21:31.115 --> 21:32.291
LIEUTENANT!

21:46.174 --> 21:47.610
ARE YOU SURE YOU'RE UP FOR THIS?

21:49.395 --> 21:50.526
LIEUTENANT?

21:52.093 --> 21:55.270
SIR, SCRUB THE SWIMMER'S
TRAINING FOR TODAY.

21:55.401 --> 21:57.316
-OKAY, I'LL NOTIFY RESCUE BOAT.

21:58.839 --> 22:00.667
-ALL RIGHT, COME ON, THAT'S IT.

22:02.146 --> 22:03.539
IT'S OVER.

22:03.670 --> 22:04.975
YOU CAN DO IT AGAIN.

22:05.106 --> 22:07.238
IT'S OKAY. IT'S ALL RIGHT.

22:35.876 --> 22:38.574
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

23:27.318 --> 23:28.407
-STEPHANIE.

23:36.197 --> 23:37.416
I CHECKED AT HEADQUARTERS.

23:38.852 --> 23:40.593
THEY SAID YOU MIGHT BE HERE.

23:47.382 --> 23:49.645
STEPHANIE, YOU'VE GOT
NOTHING TO BE ASHAMED OF.

23:52.256 --> 23:54.084
IT'S DAMN SCARY UP THERE.

23:56.478 --> 23:58.698
ESPECIALLY WHEN YOU'RE GETTING
BUFFETED BY THOSE WINDS.

24:00.569 --> 24:02.005
-IT WASN'T THE WIND.

24:03.442 --> 24:04.791
I WISH IT HAD BEEN.

24:06.749 --> 24:08.447
I WISH IT WERE THAT SIMPLE.

24:13.060 --> 24:16.150
WHEN I WAS SEVEN,

24:18.152 --> 24:20.459
MY FATHER DIED IN
A HELICOPTER CRASH.

24:22.548 --> 24:23.505
IN VIETNAM.

24:26.682 --> 24:28.467
FOR YEARS I HAD
NIGHTMARES WHENEVER I SAW

24:28.597 --> 24:30.294
NEWS FOOTAGE ABOUT THE WAR.

24:30.947 --> 24:31.861
AND...

24:33.733 --> 24:36.649
I DEVELOPED THIS DEATHLY
FEAR OF HELICOPTERS.

24:39.260 --> 24:40.827
AND THEN I WENT
TO WASHINGTON DC,

24:42.089 --> 24:43.917
I SAW HIS NAME ON THE WALL,

24:45.048 --> 24:46.702
AND THE NIGHTMARES STOPPED.

24:49.096 --> 24:51.490
AND I THOUGHT I'D COME
TO TERMS WITH LOSING HIM.

24:58.453 --> 24:59.846
BUT THEN THE OTHER DAY,

25:02.718 --> 25:05.199
WHEN YOU SWOOPED OVER
US ON THE SCARAB,

25:11.248 --> 25:12.989
IT ALL CAME BACK.

25:16.427 --> 25:20.127
WITH SUCH A VENGEANCE.

25:23.696 --> 25:25.567
-MAYBE THE BEST WAY
TO DEAL WITH THAT FEAR

25:25.698 --> 25:26.829
IS TO CONFRONT IT HEAD ON.

25:29.963 --> 25:31.355
YOU DON'T STRIKE ME AS A WOMAN

25:31.486 --> 25:33.444
WHO BACKS DOWN FROM ANYTHING.

25:35.185 --> 25:36.970
I THINK YOU SHOULD GET
RIGHT BACK UP THERE.

25:38.188 --> 25:39.320
-NO.

25:43.280 --> 25:47.328
I JUST NEED A LITTLE MORE
TIME, OKAY? TO REGROUP.

25:49.504 --> 25:50.461
-OKAY.

26:03.039 --> 26:03.997
-HEY, BRO.

26:04.737 --> 26:06.956
LET'S GO, COME ON.

26:15.443 --> 26:17.140
-CLAYMORE MINES,

26:19.273 --> 26:23.799
GRENADES, MORTARS,

26:26.062 --> 26:27.629
AKS.

26:30.066 --> 26:30.980
EXCELLENT.

26:32.155 --> 26:33.287
GET IT ALL ON BOARD;

26:34.114 --> 26:35.855
WE GOT TO GET BACK
TO LA BEFORE DAWN.

26:40.381 --> 26:43.036
-DON'T PEOPLE REALIZE WHAT
THOSE NETS CAN DO TO SEA LIONS?

26:43.166 --> 26:45.081
-GOOD THING THEY HAVE
US LOOKING OUT FOR THEM.

26:47.040 --> 26:50.434
-YOU'RE WELCOME! [BARKS]

26:53.176 --> 26:54.221
[LAUGHTER]

26:54.351 --> 26:55.657
COME ON, SAY GOODBYE TO THEM.

26:55.788 --> 26:56.963
-YEAH, GOODBYE.

26:57.093 --> 26:58.007
-COME ON.

26:58.138 --> 27:01.576
GOODBYE! [BARKS]

27:01.707 --> 27:02.533
[LAUGHTER]

27:02.664 --> 27:03.926
-YOU'RE CRAZY.

27:07.060 --> 27:08.627
-[BARKS]

27:10.803 --> 27:14.067
-SO, YOU NEVER TOLD ME HOW
IT WENT WITH THE COASTGUARD.

27:15.068 --> 27:16.069
READY TO ENLIST?

27:17.200 --> 27:18.767
-NO, NOT IN THE NEAR FUTURE.

27:18.898 --> 27:20.943
I'M VERY HAPPY WHERE
I AM, THANK YOU.

27:21.074 --> 27:22.989
-WELL, WHAT ABOUT
THE RESCUE SWIMMER?

27:24.294 --> 27:25.295
-WHAT ABOUT HIM?

27:26.470 --> 27:28.690
-WELL, SUMMER SAID HE
HAS THE HOTS FOR YOU.

27:29.430 --> 27:30.910
ARE YOU GONNA GO OUT WITH HIM?

27:31.824 --> 27:32.955
-I ALREADY DID.

27:33.564 --> 27:35.088
WE HAD DINNER LAST NIGHT.

27:35.218 --> 27:37.046
-OH-OH! AND...

27:37.177 --> 27:38.134
-AND WHAT?

27:38.265 --> 27:39.222
[LAUGHTER]

27:39.353 --> 27:40.876
-IS THERE ANOTHER DATE?

27:41.007 --> 27:42.573
-LOOK, COULD WE TALK ABOUT
SOMETHING ELSE, PLEASE.

27:42.704 --> 27:44.271
LIKE MAYBE YOUR PERSONAL LIFE.

27:44.401 --> 27:46.012
-OH, MY PERSONAL LIFE?

27:47.056 --> 27:48.449
SORRY, I DON'T HAVE ONE.

27:48.579 --> 27:51.104
-OH, PLEASE! [LAUGHS]
-LET ME TAKE OVER.

27:52.932 --> 27:54.237
-[BARKS]

27:54.368 --> 27:56.544
-[LAUGHTER]

28:02.593 --> 28:04.334
-WE'RE SITTING DUCKS OUT
HERE IN BROAD DAYLIGHT.

28:04.465 --> 28:05.814
-I GOTTA WAIT UNTIL
THE ENGINE COOLS

28:05.945 --> 28:07.555
SO I CAN SEE WHAT'S WRONG.

28:19.698 --> 28:21.134
-I KNEW IT! I KNEW IT!

28:21.264 --> 28:22.744
-WHAT'S THE MATTER?

28:22.875 --> 28:24.833
-THERE'S A COASTGUARD
PATROL BOAT OUT THERE.

28:25.747 --> 28:28.402
-WELL, GET IN THERE!
FIX THE ENGINE!

28:30.186 --> 28:33.886
-NICHOLS, ANY WORD FROM
DISTRICT ON OUR SIGHTING REPORT?

28:34.016 --> 28:36.236
THEY WANT ME TO BOARD THIS GUY?

28:36.366 --> 28:39.152
-NOT YET, CHIEF, THEY'RE
STILL TALKING TO THE ATF.

28:39.282 --> 28:41.197
GROUP IS ASKING US TO
TAKE THE RADIOGUARD

28:41.328 --> 28:43.417
FOR THE SIX-FIVE-FOUR-THREE.

28:44.548 --> 28:45.549
-VERY WELL.

28:48.465 --> 28:49.553
-WE THREW A ROD.

28:49.684 --> 28:50.990
ENGINE'S A TOTAL LOSS.

28:51.120 --> 28:52.339
-SO IS OUR CARGO.

28:54.950 --> 28:57.257
WE CAN'T RISK GETTING
BOARDED BY THE COASTGUARD.

28:59.650 --> 29:00.782
ABANDON SHIP.

29:10.313 --> 29:13.926
-COMMANDER, I'VE GOT THE
SEVEN-THREE WITH SECURE TRAFFIC
ON RADIO.

29:14.056 --> 29:15.579
CHIEF CLARK WOULD LIKE TO
BRIEF YOU ON SOMETHING.

29:15.710 --> 29:16.929
-ROGER, SWITCHING.

29:19.453 --> 29:22.325
SEVEN-THREE, THIS IS
SIX-FIVE-FOUR-THREE.
GO AHEAD, CHIEF.

29:22.456 --> 29:25.589
-ROGER, SIX-FIVE-FOUR-THREE,
WE HAVE A VESSEL
UNDER SURVEILLANCE,

29:25.720 --> 29:29.158
DIW, ABOUT FOUR MILES
WEST OF OUR POSITION.

29:29.942 --> 29:31.465
IF YOU DON'T HAVE URGENT
BUSINESS ELSEWHERE,

29:31.595 --> 29:32.858
WE'D APPRECIATE YOUR SUPPORT.

29:32.988 --> 29:34.381
DO WE HAVE YOUR
RADIOGUARD, OVER?

29:34.511 --> 29:35.991
-NO PROBLEM, CHIEF. OUT.

29:37.340 --> 29:38.777
-THE FIRE'S SET. LET'S GO.

29:38.907 --> 29:40.387
-ALL RIGHT, LET'S GET
THIS THING IN THE WATER.

29:42.258 --> 29:44.652
AND TAKE A HEADING TO SHORE
SO WE'LL LOSE THE COASTGUARD.

30:01.625 --> 30:03.410
-STEPHANIE, CHECK IT OUT.

30:12.114 --> 30:13.507
-SCARAB ONE TO SCARAB TWO,
COME IN SCARAB TWO.

30:14.943 --> 30:16.423
-NEWMAN HERE.

30:16.553 --> 30:18.773
-WE HAVE A BURNING VESSEL
OFF LONG BEACH HARBOR.

30:18.904 --> 30:19.992
WE'RE GONNA NEED YOUR HELP.

30:20.644 --> 30:21.689
-YOU GOT IT.

30:23.517 --> 30:25.388
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

30:34.876 --> 30:36.008
-GUNMOUNT ONE.

30:37.357 --> 30:39.838
-SIX-FIVE-FOUR-THREE,
THIS IS SEVEN-THREE.

30:39.968 --> 30:42.231
LOOKS LIKE OUR TARGET IS
TRYING TO SCUTTLE THE SHIP.

30:42.362 --> 30:43.450
WE'RE MOVING IN TO CHECK IT OUT.

30:43.580 --> 30:45.713
-ROGER, SEVEN-THREE,
WE'RE ON OUR WAY.

30:51.893 --> 30:53.721
-LOOK, POSSIBLE SURVIVORS!

30:58.552 --> 31:00.119
-OH, JUST OUR LUCK.

31:00.249 --> 31:01.381
IT'S THE LIFEGUARDS.

31:01.511 --> 31:02.425
WHAT DO WE DO NOW?

31:02.556 --> 31:03.774
-CUT THE ENGINE.

31:04.514 --> 31:05.646
COME ON, START WAVING YOUR ARMS.

31:06.342 --> 31:07.387
-WHAT?

31:07.517 --> 31:08.867
-DO AS I SAY.

31:08.997 --> 31:09.780
THEIR BOAT'S A LOT
FASTER THAN OURS.

31:24.578 --> 31:26.232
GOOD THING YOU SPOTTED US.

31:26.362 --> 31:27.233
-WHAT HAPPENED?

31:27.929 --> 31:28.712
-GENERATOR BLEW.

31:28.843 --> 31:30.323
STARTED AN ELECTRICAL FIRE.

31:31.150 --> 31:32.325
-AND OUR RAFT SPRUNG A LEAK.

31:45.294 --> 31:47.122
-BAYWATCH SCARAB ONE TO--
-PUT IT DOWN.

31:47.253 --> 31:48.167
NOW.

31:49.559 --> 31:50.952
GET OVER THERE.

31:51.083 --> 31:51.910
MOVE!

31:53.868 --> 31:55.000
YOU, GET OVER HERE.

31:55.130 --> 31:56.218
UNTIE THIS RAFT.

32:08.056 --> 32:09.971
LAIMBEER, GET OVER
HERE, TIE HIM UP.

32:16.717 --> 32:18.023
-WHAT ABOUT HER?

32:18.632 --> 32:20.025
-SHE STAYS WITH US.

32:31.297 --> 32:32.602
-YOU JUST CAN'T
LEAVE HIM THERE.

32:34.865 --> 32:36.041
-[COUGHING]

32:37.781 --> 32:38.913
-TIE HER UP.

32:46.703 --> 32:49.663
-NO! STEPHANIE!

32:50.707 --> 32:52.622
DON'T LEAVE ME!

32:57.366 --> 32:58.454
-HELP!

33:02.023 --> 33:03.242
STEPH!

33:15.341 --> 33:18.344
-SCARAB TWO TO SCARAB ONE,
COME IN SCARAB ONE.

33:21.260 --> 33:23.262
STEPHANIE, WHAT THE
HECK IS GOING ON?

33:23.392 --> 33:25.786
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

34:09.569 --> 34:11.049
-FORGET THE FIRE,
FORGET THE FIRE,

34:11.179 --> 34:12.746
THE LIFEGUARD BOAT
HAS BEEN HIJACKED.

34:12.876 --> 34:14.268
SUSPECTS ARE IN CONTROL.

34:14.400 --> 34:16.271
-ROGER, SIX-FIVE-FOUR-THREE.

34:16.402 --> 34:18.926
BE ADVISED, ATF
SAID THESE PEOPLE

34:19.056 --> 34:20.667
MAY HAVE BEEN SMUGGLING WEAPONS.

34:20.797 --> 34:21.972
THEY'RE PROBABLY ARMED.

34:23.974 --> 34:25.933
-SCOTT: SPEEDBOAT SOUTHBOUND
OFF OF LONG BEACH HARBOR,

34:26.063 --> 34:27.108
THIS IS THE COASTGUARD.

34:27.239 --> 34:28.283
CUT YOUR ENGINES NOW.

34:29.589 --> 34:32.373
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

35:04.058 --> 35:06.016
-YELLOW SCARAB,
CUT YOUR ENGINES.

35:12.545 --> 35:14.851
-UGH, GOD.

35:15.417 --> 35:16.375
-SIR, THEY TOOK A SHOT AT US.

35:16.505 --> 35:17.332
DANIELS HAS BEEN HIT.

35:17.463 --> 35:18.812
-CHECK HIM OUT AND HANG ON.

35:27.386 --> 35:30.171
-SEVEN-THREE, WE'RE TRYING TO
HERD THE SUSPECTS TOWARD YOU.

35:30.302 --> 35:31.520
YOUR PRESENT COURSE
SHOULD INTERCEPT.

35:34.610 --> 35:35.698
-ROGER, WE'VE GOT HIM IN SIGHT.

35:36.308 --> 35:37.439
-BAYWATCH SCARAB, COME LEFT.

35:37.570 --> 35:39.049
TRY TO KEEP HIM FROM
HEADING ONSHORE.

35:39.659 --> 35:41.269
BUT STAY OUT OF GUNSHOT RANGE.

35:41.400 --> 35:43.880
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

36:37.325 --> 36:40.198
-COASTGUARD: CUT YOUR ENGINES,
PUT YOUR HANDS IN THE AIR.

36:50.599 --> 36:53.211
DROP YOUR WEAPONS, MOVE
TO THE BOW OF THE BOAT.

36:59.173 --> 37:01.915
-WEAPONS ON THE DECK,
HANDS IN THE AIR, MOVE!

37:02.481 --> 37:04.483
-GET TO THE FRONT
OF THE BOAT. DO IT!

37:06.833 --> 37:08.095
-CLEAR!

37:11.272 --> 37:14.362
-GET TO THE FRONT. GET TO
THE FRONT! GET ON UP THERE!

37:14.493 --> 37:16.408
-DOWN ON YOUR KNEES!

37:16.538 --> 37:18.497
-THEY DUMPED MY PARTNER
OVERBOARD BACK BY
THE FISHING BOAT.

37:18.627 --> 37:20.020
WILL YOU GET THE HELICOPTER
TO GO LOOK FOR HIM?

37:20.150 --> 37:21.195
-CAN DO.

37:21.326 --> 37:22.631
-IS SCOTT DANIELS ON THAT CREW?

37:22.762 --> 37:24.111
-HE'S ON BOARD
BUT HE'S BEEN SHOT.

37:24.242 --> 37:25.199
HE WAS WOUNDED BY
ONE OF THESE GUYS.

37:25.330 --> 37:26.896
-SHOT! IS HE OKAY?

37:27.027 --> 37:28.463
-COASTGUARD: HE'S ALL RIGHT.
-CAN I TALK TO HIM?

37:28.594 --> 37:30.030
-WE'LL GET YOU HOOKED UP.
THE RADIO'S OVER HERE.

37:31.597 --> 37:32.772
-WE'RE GONNA NEED YOUR HELP.

37:32.902 --> 37:34.339
-GO AHEAD, LIEUTENANT.

37:34.469 --> 37:36.297
SCOTT, WE'VE GOT TO
BACK AND LOOK FOR MATT.

37:36.428 --> 37:37.864
HE'S IN TROUBLE,
CAN YOU LET ME UP?

37:37.994 --> 37:39.518
-SOUNDS GOOD,
PREPARE FOR HOIST.

37:39.648 --> 37:41.650
-MY PILOT'S GIVING
ME A THUMBS UP.

37:41.781 --> 37:42.956
STAND BY TO BE HOISTED.

37:43.086 --> 37:44.740
YOU'LL HAVE TO BE
OUR RESCUE SWIMMER.

37:44.871 --> 37:46.438
I'VE GOT A SHRAPNEL WOUND.

37:47.090 --> 37:51.834
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

37:58.319 --> 37:59.842
ALL RIGHT, YOU SURE ABOUT THIS?

37:59.973 --> 38:02.192
-MY FRIEND'S OUT THERE;
I DON'T HAVE MUCH CHOICE.

38:04.282 --> 38:06.545
-USE MY GEAR, SOME
OF IT WILL FIT YOU.

38:26.782 --> 38:28.262
-ARGH.

38:28.393 --> 38:30.220
-I THOUGHT YOU SAID
IT WAS JUST A SCRATCH.

38:30.351 --> 38:31.047
-DON'T WORRY ABOUT
ME, CONCENTRATE ON
WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

38:44.452 --> 38:47.281
-I HAVE A CONTACT. PERSON
IN THE WATER, 3:00.

38:56.290 --> 38:57.683
-SWIMMER READY.

39:01.121 --> 39:02.383
YOU CAN DO IT.

39:04.733 --> 39:08.563
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

39:50.300 --> 39:51.476
-I'VE GOT YOU!

39:51.606 --> 39:52.912
I'VE GOT YOU, MATT.

39:53.042 --> 39:55.262
-[COUGHING]

40:16.326 --> 40:17.719
-[LAUGHING]

40:18.590 --> 40:20.766
-GOOD!
-OH, HERE WE GO.
HERE WE GO. HERE WE GO!

40:24.291 --> 40:25.510
WELL, IT'S GETTING BETTER.

40:26.032 --> 40:27.860
-WELL, THIS EGG
ROLL IS DELICIOUS.

40:27.990 --> 40:29.470
-HERE, TRY IT WITH
SOME OF THE SAUCE.

40:29.601 --> 40:30.863
-NO, NO, NOT IF IT'S SPICY.

40:32.081 --> 40:34.040
-YOU DON'T LIKE SPICY FOOD?

40:34.170 --> 40:37.826
-NO, I DON'T. [LAUGHS]
YOU DO, I KNEW IT!
YOU LIKE SPICY FOOD!

40:37.957 --> 40:39.741
-I HATE SPICY FOOD.
IT GIVES ME HEARTBURN.

40:39.872 --> 40:41.090
-GOOD.

40:41.874 --> 40:42.918
-[LAUGHTER]

40:43.702 --> 40:46.444
I CAN'T BELIEVE HOW
MUCH WE HAVE IN COMMON.

40:48.576 --> 40:52.145
I MEAN, BEING OPEN
AND TALKING LIKE THIS,

40:52.275 --> 40:54.234
THIS HAS NEVER
HAPPENED TO ME BEFORE.

40:56.105 --> 40:59.195
-I THINK YOU'RE A VERY
INTERESTING MAN, SCOTT DANIELS.

40:59.805 --> 41:01.589
AND I LIKE BEING WITH YOU.

41:03.417 --> 41:04.287
-SO WHAT'S NEXT?

41:04.940 --> 41:06.507
HOW OFTEN DO WE SEE EACH OTHER?

41:08.204 --> 41:09.118
ON THE WEEKENDS?

41:10.729 --> 41:11.817
A COUPLE OF TIMES A WEEK?

41:12.948 --> 41:14.428
EVERY DAY?

41:14.863 --> 41:19.389
-[LAUGHS] LET'S JUST SEE IF
WE CAN MAKE IT THROUGH LUNCH.
